  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Following 510(k) clearance, the indicated patient population was extended to include pediatric patients (body surface area 0.5–1.2 m²) with correspondingly lower flow rates (0.8–2.5 L/min) and higher rotational speeds (up to 4 200 RPM). The validation campaign predates this extension; existing validation results are cited as providing adequate coverage on the basis that the hemolysis power-law exponent is assumed flow-regime-independent.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Medium",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/morrison-cpb-hemolysis-mrl2",
